        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="5">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid property damage, personal injury or death, park the vehicle on a flat level surface,
                        set the parking brake, chock the wheels and turn the engine off.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">The Evaporator assembly has two bolts holding the accumulator and bracket to the side of
                    the evaporator as shown in Figure 1. The two bolts must be removed prior to installation of the
                    reinforcement kit to allow clearance/free play.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0416011" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0416011.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="368px"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Accumulator Mounting Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place the bracket on the side of the case with the hole aligned with the hole in the
                    case and insert the lag bolt as shown in Figure 2.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0416012" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0416012.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="248px"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Install Bracket</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the lag bolt (Figure 3) to 25 to 30 Lbf-in (3 Nm).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0416013" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0416013.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="288px"/>
                <caption>Figure 3. Tighten Lag Bolt</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place the hose clamp around the accumulator and over the bracket leg along the
                    accumulator side (Figure 4). Tighten the hose clamp.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0416014" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0416014.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="256px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 4. Install Hose Clamp</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Replace the accumulator bolts and tighten to 50 Lbf-in (6 Nm). The completed
                    installation is shown in Figure 5.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0316015" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0416015.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 5. Completed Installation</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
